headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama has commanded a lot of the headlines in the NBA offseason.
headlines.shortLinkText: PJ Washington scores 25, rookie Brandon Miller provides spark as Hornets top Hawks 116-110 in opener

headlines.description: — The Indiana Pacers signed Bruce Brown for his defense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bruce Brown boosts Pacers offense as Indiana routs Washington 143-120 in record-setting opener

events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis showed against his old team why his new one is an NBA Finals favorite.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis makes tiebreaking 3-pointer in strong Celtics debut, helps Boston beat Knicks 108-104

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 20 points and eight rebounds, and the Orlando Magic beat the Houston Rockets 116-86 on Wednesday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cole Anthony scores 20 points to help Orlando Magic beat Houston Rockets 116-86 in opener

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 10 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter, and Cleveland beat the Brooklyn Nets 114-113 on Wednesday night for the Cavaliers' first road win in a season opener since 2000.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 27 points as Cavaliers top Nets 114-113 in season opener

headlines.description: — To open a new season, the Miami Heat revisited their go-to move from last season: winning close games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat waste almost all of 19-point lead, scramble to hold off Pistons 103-102

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 22 points in his Toronto debut, O.G. Anunoby had 20 and the Raptors gave new coach Darko Rajakovic a victory in his first game by beating the Minnesota Timberwolves 97-94 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder scores 22, Anunoby has 20 as Raptors beat Timberwolves 97-94 in season opener

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — With a promising young core, the Oklahoma City Thunder have their sights set on the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 points as Thunder beat Bulls 124-104 in season opener

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 24 points, Zion Williamson added 23 points and seven rebounds as the New Orleans Pelicans defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 111-104 on Wednesday night in the season-opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: CJ McCollum and Zion Williamson lead Pelicans past Grizzlies 111-104 in season opener

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 33 points to lead the Sacramento Kings to a 130-114 victory over the Utah Jazz on Wednesday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harrison Barnes scores 33, powers Kings past Jazz 130-114 in season opener

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks spoil Victor Wembanyama's NBA debut, beat the Spurs 126-119 in the teams' opener

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 27 points and Kawhi Leonard added 23 to lead five players in double figures as the Los...
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard and George dominate in Clippers' 123-111 win over the Trail Blazers to open the season
